description:
&lt;p&gt;NECS works across the UK to support health and social care customers in meeting strategic and operational challenges, to improve outcomes and increase efficiency. We deliver a diverse range of services to organisations working within health and social care across the North of England and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NECS combines specialist skills and expertise with scale and resilience to achieve required results. Many of our people have extensive NHS and public sector experience and we combine core NHS values with a sharp focus on customer care and a relentless pursuit of continuous improvement. We very much see ourselves as a key partner in the future success of the healthcare system and we take our share of the responsibility for shaping effective delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;About the teams&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Digital Applications Team is made up of multi-disciplined individuals working mainly within the .Net Core and Framework in C#.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Front end development is a combination of HTML, CSS and JavaScript, with Angular and Bootstrap as the preferred client-side frameworks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Azure DevOps is used for Version Control, Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We undertake mobile projects using Xamarin along with other options, and might also take on work using a custom technology stack at the client’s request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;Main purpose of role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Software Tester you will work alongside an evolving team with the responsibility with ensuring standards and quality are kept to a high level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be able to demonstrate an ability to plan and structure their work from initiation through specification to final testing - whilst considering the real-time needs of the business. Being flexible enough to react to the rapidly changing demands of their operation is essential, therefore the ideal individual will be able to think quickly, plan carefully and be able to rapidly deploy robust, well-tested solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;Activities include&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop and implement design test frameworks and strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Analysing requirements/user stories and design of manual or automated tests with acceptance criteria to ensure the software under test meets those requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adhere to best practice and develop proactive solutions based on feedback from customer, developers and users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participate in development of test execution, defect recording and capture of test results. This may include the development and use of manual and automated test scripts, or UAT activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Testing across multiple platforms and devices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Summarise results of test execution into test reports, during and on completion of testing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop high value automated tests, write automation code, and mentor other in creating and maintaining their own.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Undertake investigation into underlying issues with Automated Tests and manage them through to resolution across programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensure relevant processes are in place to ensure automated tests are maintained across projects and service lines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensure return on investment is obtained from automated tests, optimising best value and reducing waste across programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;Advantages of working with NECS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Visual Studio (MSDN) Subscription and associated benefits&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work with the latest Microsoft technologies and services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Continuous development and accreditation opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Generous holiday allowance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS pension scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary sacrifice car scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to NHS discounts with major retailers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our main offices are in Durham City, Sheffield and Chester and there may be occasions where travel is required e.g. customer meetings or other NECS site visits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately we are unable to offer Tier 2 sponsorship to any candidate that requires a visa to work in the UK.&lt;/p&gt;
